Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.28,0:00:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd like amplified or clarified, we'll do that.\NWe've got a few remaining minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.90,0:01:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So yes, oh, yeah, in a way that was going to come up next time when we talk about truth.\NBut I want you to also see that real is what you define as the qualifying, the qualification
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.45,0:01:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of real.\NIs real what is scientifically provable?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.28,0:01:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is real what's experiential?\NSo real in a way is a way of approaching the subject, the defining the overall context
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,by which we call it.\NReal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.15,0:01:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a reality that exists independent of human observation?\NQuantum mechanics says no.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.06,0:01:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole universe is merely a consequence of observation.\NWhether it's real really infers whether it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.28,0:02:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists.\NAnd then how you define what exists is where the error comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.70,0:02:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that I have a foot is a subjective conclusion, actually.\NYou can't prove you have a foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.37,0:02:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But you experience it.\NSo there is an experiential reality independent of what somebody might say about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.24,0:02:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So somebody might say that's not really a foot.\NThat's a hoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.65,0:02:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In their language it's a hoof.\NIt's a hoof of a foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.12,0:02:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So anything that I . . . Is it really a . . .\NAt a certain level it's all an illusion, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because you're interpreting reality as what exists as form.\NSo you're talking about physical reality, physical existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.90,0:02:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you physically exist is a statement of truth because you can then verify that\Nexperientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What that means, however, is something else.\NThat's more abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How you define that reality?\NThe reality itself is independent of definition or how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.59,0:03:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How you see the stare.\NThe stare is independent of how you perceive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.19,0:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But . . . . So then you call it . . . You think, well, eyes go through shape.\NYeah.
