Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.71,0:24:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Oxford four and various numbers of them you know were extremely good and\Nit's cost all of us our own security I mean it's why you know we're lined up at
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.59,0:25:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,airports because some guy had a shoe bomb tied to his shoe and you know yeah\Nwell all of our lives have been impaired by the consequences of double
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.56,0:25:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,personalities the fact that they're one is secured and one secured is not\Nsecured is extremely important yeah so very often if we run into a paradox
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.76,0:25:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,about a person always the nicest person in the world and then you find that\Nthey're you're right
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.34,0:25:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nhorrible blogs if I always got two personalities right that's that's so one
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.54,0:25:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at one lumber and one calibrates at another it's like most two\Npersonalities in the same body and one psyche takes over sometimes and another
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.11,0:25:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,psyche takes over other times yes yes it can be very dangerous it can be very\Ndangerous because the downside one may cause the upside one is life because of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.86,0:26:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside one you become executed\Nand the upside person gets executed because of what the downside person did
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.00,0:26:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know so it's an interesting thing I've only known a few well no I've known\Nquite a few in practice and practiced and in personal life I've run across
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.16,0:26:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,them each time with a devastating consequence frankly what did you\Ncalibrate Bush Cheney and Bill Clinton I don't remember the sweetheart it's in the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.98,0:26:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,book you know see you have\NIt depends on you asking what role, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.55,0:26:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As a person, what is this calibrated at?\NAs a functionary in this title, what does he function at?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.61,0:26:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people may be saintly and very bad at the helm.\NOther people may be very good at the helm,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.81,0:27:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can't trust them with your wife, you know what I'm saying?\NI wonder who that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.10,0:27:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't think anybody agrees with how certain decisions\Nmade by the government have turned out, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.07,0:27:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think the person himself can be quite, you know, integrous.\NBut because you're integrous doesn't mean you can't be mistaken, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.75,0:27:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.11,0:27:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou show the word what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.29,0:27:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt?\NYes, what about doubt?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.57,0:27:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt?\NYes, doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.13,0:28:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's sort of, to some degree, along with skepticism.\NWell, doubt has to do with uncertainty,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.05,0:28:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is often a very logical and realistic to be doubtful.\NIt means I don't have enough information yet to make up a mind, in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.06,0:28:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A sophisticated person holds all information as being tentative.\NAll information is tentative.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.27,0:28:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.23,0:28:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTo be confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.47,0:28:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All information...\NA mature person knows that there is yet more to be known.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.20,0:28:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you know about a thing, there's still more to know.\NTherefore, all information is held as tentative.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.00,0:28:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I hold everything I say as tentative.\NIt's the truth to the best that we can discern it at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.94,0:28:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that we won't be able to improve upon it,\Nbecause otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.92,0:29:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of mankind would be stationary, you know, it would be stationary.\NMore will be discovered later, is a great likelihood, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.90,0:29:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There is yet more to be known, no matter how complete we think our knowledge is.\NAnd you see this, you know, 25 years after a war,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.98,0:29:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, some Japanese scientists were working on nuclear energy,\Nand were very close to an atomic bomb, and we didn't even know it at the time we dropped the bomb on Hiroshima,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.99,0:29:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and Nagasaki, that Professor Nagasaki, and the professor, I forget his name now,\Nwhose papers have just been revealed in recent years by his wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.57,0:29:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they were very, very extremely close to an actual atomic bomb,\Nand if we hadn't dropped it, they would have dropped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.53,0:29:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's more to know.\N25, 50 years after a war, critical elements are still being discovered, you know, critical elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.96,0:30:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So all information...\NAll information and knowledge is subject to revision.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.74,0:30:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Subject to revision.\NPartly because of the evolution of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.18,0:30:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So certain things are not known, but then as the field rises, as the field lifts,\Nnow that reveals access to things that would not have been thought about before.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.23,0:30:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if I was running the CIA etc., I would use consciousness calibration,\Nand frankly, I would take all the people in critical...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.50,0:30:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,levels, just have a photo of them and\Ncheck them all with the arm and see if there's any double
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.30,0:30:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,personalities in there. There's somebody\Nthat has another agenda.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.41,0:30:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I trust them with, you know,\Nthe highest possible secrets in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.43,0:30:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I would run them through\Na quick screen. Very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.38,0:30:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't cost anything.\NYeah. Speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.07,0:31:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand the question.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.29,0:31:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, truth is one\Nyou might say an attribute of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.78,0:31:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,God is\Nomniscient, omnipresent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.01,0:31:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Omniscient and omnipresent.\NSo, omniscience
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.96,0:31:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is an attribute of divinity.\NOmniscience has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.35,0:31:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness of truth about all\Nthings. So, only the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.79,0:31:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,field of consciousness is\Naccessible to us
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.48,0:31:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as humans.\NIn other realms, truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.66,0:31:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a prevailing reality. Here it is not a\Nprevailing reality. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.00,0:32:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the omniscience of God then is\Na
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.25,0:32:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,one way to God is\Nby calibrating levels of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.99,0:32:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and following those things\Nwhich calibrate the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.88,0:32:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In as much as we're born without that\Ncapacity for discernment,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.00,0:32:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we have now\Na methodology. We don't know altitude
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.57,0:32:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by looking at a mountain either.\NBut we now have altimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.81,0:32:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the advancement of human consciousness\Nhas shown us
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.54,0:32:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a different way.\NA better way. One that's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.63,0:32:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal. And I want to\Nemphasize again, it's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.30,0:32:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any personal feeling about any of the calibrations\Nwe do at all. I don't have any personal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.08,0:32:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration about it at all, correctly.\NIt's just whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.39,0:32:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is whatever it is. You know, like an altimeter,\Nyou go up to the mountain and you read the dial.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.89,0:32:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with consciousness calibration\Nwe just read the dial.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.32,0:32:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't personally have any investment in\Nwhat the answer is one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.26,0:32:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if it comes out\Ndifferent than what one expects,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.24,0:33:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that leads one to\Nimportant discoveries.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.48,0:33:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NIf there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.77,0:33:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,differential between your expectation\Nand the result that you get, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.96,0:33:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then that leads you to further\Ninquiry. And with further inquiry, then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.40,0:33:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you do discover the truth behind it.\NNow, the question
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.92,0:33:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was how do you differentiate between\Ndivinity, reality, and truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.11,0:33:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what it is?\NWe said that reality is that which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.01,0:33:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is confirmable.\NConfirmable. So, then you have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.24,0:33:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,truth which has to do with\Nessence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.38,0:33:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And reality has to do with\Ncontent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.79,0:33:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is confirmable.\NWhat is confirmable?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.59,0:33:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's linear.\NIt's here,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.78,0:33:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at this time, and it weighs this much,\Nand it measures this much, and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.78,0:33:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,located right here.\NSo, that's all linear, confirmable.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.03,0:34:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's content\Nof consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.20,0:34:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is of a different level. Truth has to\Ndo with abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.40,0:34:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth is what escapes\Npeople who are,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.61,0:34:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you say,\Npedestrian, pedestrian, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.61,0:34:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They get the pedestrian\Nlimited content,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.61,0:34:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't get the meaning.\NTherefore, what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.61,0:34:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know what it means, because\Nthe mind at that point
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.67,0:34:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,has not reached the capacity\Nof abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.67,0:34:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, abstract thought\Nis of a higher level than concrete
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.67,0:34:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,mundane thought.\NProvability has nothing to do with meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.67,0:34:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning is an\Nabstract. So, meaning has to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.71,0:34:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,do with the context, contextual\Nunderstanding of the significance of the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.71,0:34:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning. And much of\Nspiritual work is the revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.75,0:34:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly of significance and meaning.\NYou say, God, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.75,0:34:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the inference? And then suddenly\Nyou stand
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.75,0:35:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,back and you suddenly get, oh wow,\Nyou suddenly see the significance of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.75,0:35:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole thing.\NAnd if you were going to explain this to somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.75,0:35:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,else you would find it difficult, because\Nhow can you put the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.75,0:35:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,into a linear content? That's been the\Ntrouble with describing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.19,0:35:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth throughout the ages.\NHow can you put the non-linear into
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.19,0:35:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,language when language is\Nprimarily linear?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.19,0:35:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you speak of the ineffable,\Nyou speak
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.44,0:35:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the mystical.\NThe mystic is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.55,0:35:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,one whose consciousness\Nis dominated by a field,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.55,0:35:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not by\Nthe content of the field, but by the field
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.92,0:35:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, by which\Neverything is recontextualized,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.15,0:35:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,yes? So,\Ntruth is an abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.53,0:35:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can take facts\Nand then from these facts you get meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.53,0:35:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you get\Nwhat is the truth of this, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.53,0:36:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, truth is a higher level of\Nabstraction. So, in the great books
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.30,0:36:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world, you see,\Nthe various levels
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.30,0:36:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of comprehension are laid out pretty\Nmuch, you see? There's
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.34,0:36:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the concrete, the literal, then there's\Nthe inference, and then the higher
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.34,0:36:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and higher levels of abstract\Ntruth. The Kant, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.34,0:36:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Kant, Manuel Kant's\Nlevels of categories. And what you see
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.34,0:36:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with relativism, for instance,\Nis there's no respect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.34,0:36:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for categories. They think\Nyou can just, you know, mix one category
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.34,0:36:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with another one because it suits your political\Npurpose. And
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.34,0:36:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the laws of logic are you cannot\Nmix levels, you cannot mix levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.34,0:36:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is true on one level is not true\Non another level. What is true
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.34,0:36:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on one level is not true on another level.\NAnd so, one error
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.44,0:36:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that people do make,\Nyou know, especially critics of spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.44,0:36:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is they don't respect\Nthe Kantian categories,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.50,0:36:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of abstraction of\Ntruth and logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.50,0:37:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is only true at\Nits own level.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.03,0:37:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to make\Nit wrong, what is done politically is to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.13,0:37:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,take it from this level, put it in this level,\Nand then do a make wrong on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.13,0:37:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDoes that explain it well enough? Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.44,0:37:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the explanation is more\Ncomplicated than the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.69,0:37:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation to begin with.\NYes, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.55,0:37:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt sometimes is very critical to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.09,0:37:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As I just said, your very\Nexistence is currently under threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.69,0:37:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Your existence is not guaranteed\Nwhatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.88,0:38:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's because of a compartmentalized\Nsplit personality. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.88,0:38:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it is very critical.\NAnd the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.88,0:38:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I know to diagnose it\Nis to begin to suspect it, that there seems
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.88,0:38:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to be two sides to this person's personality.\NThere seems to be a puzzlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.88,0:38:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the people\Nare aware of it, sometimes they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.07,0:38:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Great disparities in behaviors\Nand the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.07,0:38:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes about\Nreally from clinical sophistication
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.42,0:38:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin to suspect it, frankly.\NFirst of all, you have to even know
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.42,0:38:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that it exists and that it's a very\Nimportant thing to know at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.80,0:38:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To even know that it exists.\NCompartmentalized personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.80,0:38:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We know, pretty much everybody's\Nheard about multiple personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.80,0:38:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know,\Na very discrete split personality
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.80,0:38:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is very often\Nbetween one that calibrates very low
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.80,0:39:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other one calibrates high.\NIt's like the angelic and the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.80,0:39:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,demonic were both heading for this body\Nand they both got there at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.80,0:39:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow.\NTwo spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.80,0:39:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in only one body.\NSo I'm sure there's peculiar karmic propensities
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.80,0:39:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which I don't know and I've never\Nresearched.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.80,0:39:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, the split personalities I've known\Nin my personal life have been very unpleasant,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.80,0:39:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly, because they get into your life\Nwith their benign, isn't he a wonderful person
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.80,0:39:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next thing you know\Nthey're putting a knife in your back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.80,0:39:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you never suspected it.\NThey can have a very, very, very
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.80,0:39:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,devastating effect on your life.\NYeah, very devastating.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.63,0:39:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nvery often it's met with denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.76,0:39:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll say that, you know, so and so\Nand then they give you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.84,0:39:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,some reading on their negative side\Nand you say, oh no, oh no,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.84,0:39:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're so sure the way your perception\Nis correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.84,0:39:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you always hold in mind that there could be an alternate side\Nto a personality
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.84,0:40:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're not always\Nthe same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.03,0:40:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDuring the lecture you spoke of the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.00,0:40:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NNo, you just become the witness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.82,0:40:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the experiencer.\NThe experiencer is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.98,0:40:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,tries to milk everything\Nto ensure its own survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.03,0:40:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the witness\Nof the ego doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.11,0:40:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the witness\Nof the observer. So you're detached
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.11,0:40:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then from subjectively\Nidentifying yourself with the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.11,0:40:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinarily the mind\Nthinks, well I am that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.17,0:40:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing.\NInstead of I am the consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.17,0:41:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer, the witness\Nof the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.17,0:41:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're more detached when you see\Nyourself as the witness observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.17,0:41:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how do you know\Nthat you're the witness observer?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.26,0:41:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness observer then is coming out\Nof the consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.26,0:41:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of consciousness\Nitself that you're capable
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.30,0:41:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of having a witness observer.\NMuch less an experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.30,0:41:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To have no thought\Nabout what goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.75,0:41:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes about\Nthrough a contemplative lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.88,0:41:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you end up\Nthinking about a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.15,0:41:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,only if you choose to think about it.\NIf you say, well I think
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.32,0:41:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll think about this, then you think about it.\NBut you don't think about it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.32,0:41:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,against\Nyour own choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.42,0:41:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that comes about\Nas a contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.48,0:41:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,where the field\Nis aware of the content of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.05,0:42:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's aware\Nonly out of its being a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.05,0:42:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not out of its being\Na particular you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.19,0:42:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as what's being said now\Nis being witnessed. I have no idea what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.19,0:42:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.\NI hear it the same time you hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.50,0:42:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The speakingness happens\Nof its own spontaneity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.50,0:42:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as the speakingness\Nbecause that's an attribute
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.50,0:42:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you relearn\Nafter you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.92,0:42:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,lose the ability to relate to the world.\NSlowly over time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.42,0:42:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you relearn\Nand I call that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.51,0:42:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,persona. There's an aspect\Nof consciousness which then learns
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.51,0:42:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to interact with the world\Nand converse with it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.78,0:42:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and know which streetcar to get onto and all that.\NBut it has nothing to do with who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.78,0:42:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the witness.\NIt could be just somebody else in another body.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.78,0:42:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any personal\Nmeaning anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.94,0:42:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore whether you're\Ngood or bad, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.94,0:43:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the other person's problem\Nbecause it's their perception
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.94,0:43:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's got nothing to do with your own reality\Nwhich is beyond good and bad, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.94,0:43:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know\Nwho they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.96,0:43:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So as I say,\Nwhen that state first emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.96,0:43:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I would see people\Ntalking to this body
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.96,0:43:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't figure\Nwho they're talking to.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.51,0:43:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Who the hell is he talking to?\NAnd I realized they think it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.51,0:43:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NI couldn't figure out who they're talking to.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.03,0:43:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are they talking to?\NBecause the body had nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.03,0:43:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with who I am\Nor even where I was, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.26,0:43:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness may be here\Nand here's Doc's body over here
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.26,0:43:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and people are talking to this thing here.\NWhat the hell are they talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.26,0:43:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NLike out of body, I'm here
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.67,0:43:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're talking to this body here\Nand that's certainly a strange phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.67,0:44:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It took a while\Nfor people to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.11,0:44:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're talking to that\Nand that is what they assumed to be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.11,0:44:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So then you learn how to\Nvia the persona
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.11,0:44:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,become that entity\Nto the degree that is necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.11,0:44:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in a social interaction.\NIf there's no necessity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.11,0:44:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for social interaction\Nthere's no necessity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.11,0:44:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to own that persona.\NIt would just be excess baggage
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.11,0:44:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,like you don't need a raincoat\Nif it's not raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.59,0:44:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena sort of grew out of themselves.\NDon't forget there isn't any book on such a matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.59,0:44:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was just discovered\Nthrough a personal
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.59,0:44:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what the Rokoff's personal\Nsubject of awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.59,0:44:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the learning of these things.\NThey may be somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.82,0:44:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in some book\Nbut I've never read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.96,0:45:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NI need somebody to translate
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.13,0:45:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what he says.\NWith what?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.67,0:45:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well this persona interacts with\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.67,0:45:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It will say something\Nbut it is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.11,0:45:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it will say something\Nbut it's because
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.53,0:45:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the conversational\Ninteraction of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.65,0:45:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no intrinsic\Ngreat reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.65,0:45:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nbecause of the alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.92,0:45:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lovingness between the two\Neverything becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.92,0:45:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualized.\NSo no matter what the person says
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.92,0:45:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't have any\Neffect on the alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.92,0:45:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,whatsoever.\NA person could be angry at you one second
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.92,0:45:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't really mean anything\Nbecause in two seconds later it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.92,0:46:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If something was going to\Nthreaten the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.01,0:46:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that would have a different impact.\NBecause your alignment is a commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.01,0:46:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you're both aligned\Nand committed to reach God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.01,0:46:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so that makes you parallels.\NYou know
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.94,0:46:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a little static on the radio\Nis not exactly a major transmission
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.94,0:46:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at all times.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.94,0:46:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say something\Nback and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.94,0:46:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your animalness.\NDon't forget you're an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.94,0:46:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the cause for\Ndisparity is really your animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.32,0:46:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really your animal.\NAnd I'll say now
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.76,0:46:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,my animal will go in the refrigerator\Nand I say
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.76,0:46:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where in the world is the pickled herring?\NAnd her animal
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.07,0:46:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will come up and say\Nright here in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.07,0:47:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, alright.\NI don't want to mix it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.17,0:47:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a pickled herring\Nright in your eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.82,0:47:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt's never physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.03,0:47:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the nuisance\Nthe annoyance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.03,0:47:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the animal being annoyed.\NThe animal thinks there's a bone over there
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.03,0:47:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and he goes over there\Nand the bone falls down the steps
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.03,0:47:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the animal is annoyed.\NIt's the animal that's coming up
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.13,0:47:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the real you.\NThe real you hasn't changed any position.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.13,0:47:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So annoyance I think is between couples\Nis usually more the animal coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.13,0:47:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the animal coming up.\NEven wanting people to agree with you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.19,0:47:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is really your animal wanting\Nthem they should agree with you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.19,0:47:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nso if you say
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.32,0:47:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,well that's just my animal\Nit's not really who I am you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.32,0:48:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.90,0:48:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up kidding each other a good deal\Nyou know because
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.11,0:48:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you really do because what would have been\Nannoying if you kid about it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.11,0:48:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it defuses it you know what I'm saying.\NSomebody ate my last pickled herring well
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.15,0:48:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to kill them.\NI can let them live.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.21,0:48:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Gave it to the neighbor.\NGave my last pickled herring to the neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.28,0:49:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh\NI don't have to let go of my attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.42,0:49:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to pickled herring.\NCan't get to heaven because you're
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.94,0:49:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to pickled herring.\NGod says you love me more
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.28,0:49:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or pickled herring more.\NAlright
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.55,0:49:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What else needs clarification?\NYes indeed sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.19,0:49:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.57,0:49:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You see if you come from right and wrong\Nyou'd say well gee that's terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.57,0:49:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they're lying all the time. But that's their job.\NIf I ask
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.53,0:49:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about specifically let's see\NI have specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.55,0:50:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have permission to ask about\Nthe U.N. resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.80,0:50:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The politicians in the U.N.\Nlie routinely resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.80,0:50:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Routinely.\NYou know the U.N. calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.28,0:50:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were telling the truth\Nall the time it would be like 420 wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.38,0:50:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's\Nmeans it's like you're jockeying
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.07,0:50:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for a verbal rhetorical\Nposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.28,0:50:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trading\Nwhite chips for black chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.28,0:50:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a constant dealing back\Nand forth. I'll let go
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.28,0:50:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this statement if you let go that\Nstatement and if you give me this advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.28,0:50:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll let go this\Ndisadvantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.28,0:50:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wheeling and dealing. So you might say\Npolitics is wheeling and dealing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.28,0:50:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for power and\Nthe gain. Whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.84,0:50:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,gain they presume occurs.\NRight now the primary gain
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.84,0:50:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is number one oil\Nmoney and number two moral
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.84,0:51:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,high ground.\NYou hear all these
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.07,0:51:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,political arguments they're all about the moral\Nhigh ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.61,0:51:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral high ground and with it often\Ngoes the money with the oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.61,0:51:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So that has to do with survival.\NSo the politician is interested
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.40,0:51:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in survival and\Nprimarily survival of his own position.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.40,0:51:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,His own position.\NYou see people switch sides depending on which
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.40,0:51:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is popular. If this gets more votes\Nsuddenly they go in this way. When this gets more votes
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.40,0:51:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they go this way.\NSo you might say that's not a defect
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.53,0:51:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that's his job. That's what he's supposed\Nto do. If you find more people
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.30,0:51:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,like chocolate than vanilla somehow\Nyou begin to favor chocolate don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.53,0:51:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to run for president\Nyou can't be for vanilla
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.53,0:51:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when the 55%\Nprefer chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.71,0:51:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the poll tells you how you got to move\Nand I think in truth versus false
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.71,0:52:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we calibrated the\Nvarious political positions
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.71,0:52:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the political position of\Nthe electorate. If I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.71,0:52:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the electorate was at about 375.\NSo for a spiritual platform
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.71,0:52:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to work\Nthey would have to devise it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.71,0:52:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to appeal to a consciousness level\Nabout 375.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.17,0:52:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why hatred and spite don't really\Nwin elections because that calibrates to 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.17,0:52:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At 375\Nvery few people look favorably
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.17,0:52:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at hatred.\NI mean they'll tolerate it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.17,0:52:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll quote it when they want it\Nbut they don't respect it or vote for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.17,0:52:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness\Nlevel 370 I think was
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.17,0:52:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where the last electorate was.\NSo if I was devising
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.17,0:52:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a political platform\NI would devise one that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.17,0:52:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,appeals to about 375.\NThat's sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.17,0:52:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,middle of the road, whatever is sane\Nand sensible, whatever sounds ethical
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.17,0:52:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and logical\Nand sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.61,0:53:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonableness\Nand pretty much good naturedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.61,0:53:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good natured reasonableness.\NSo to win an election
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.75,0:53:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I would devise a political platform\Nand I would calibrate it at 375.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.75,0:53:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And move my positions around\Nuntil they're at 375.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.75,0:53:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see\Neven as a politician I would have to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.84,0:53:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,change what I consider to be\Nsufficiently truthful to present
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.84,0:53:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the public. Not in order to get elected.\NYou can't
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.88,0:53:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,malign the public\Nand still get elected.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.42,0:53:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to have to say what sounds favorable.\NI don't think any of them were aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.42,0:53:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They struck it by luck.\NClinton I think hit into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.42,0:53:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Clinton was in\Nhis platform was around 370 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.42,0:53:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was a big winner.\NSo avoid the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.98,0:53:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,extremes and try and hit what's\Nreasonable. 375
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.98,0:53:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and so that's also the appeal\Nof all the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.98,0:54:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual books you see in the\Ntruck stops and all. Who's the big
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.98,0:54:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Warren? Rick Warren.\NYeah. You know his
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.59,0:54:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,375 that's enthusiasm.\NIt's 375 that built the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.59,0:54:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,pyramids, that built the Empire State\NBuilding. It's enthusiastic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.59,0:54:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,good heartedness\Nand enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.59,0:54:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than just saying yes.\NIt's being yes and then being enthusiastic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.75,0:54:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,about the yes and enthusiastic.\NSo to be enthusiastic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.78,0:54:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,about that which isn't\Npretty much almost guarantees success.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.78,0:54:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost guarantees it.\NYeah. And because you're
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.07,0:54:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in a safe level of truth\Nto begin with you don't have to change your positions
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.07,0:54:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time. You don't have to constantly change\Nposition. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.15,0:54:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes doc.\NYou were on the last...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.82,0:55:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Xeno.\NOh I don't want you to ask me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.96,0:55:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Xeno you know\Nthe Xeno paradox
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.80,0:55:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was if a\Nrabbit and a tortoise start out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.96,0:55:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time\Nwhich will win the race you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.00,0:55:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And see the tortoise\Ngoes slower but the thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.00,0:55:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at any point in time\Nyou've only gone half the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.00,0:55:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at the next point in time\Nyou'll again have gone half the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.00,0:55:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You will then have gone half the distance.\NYou will then have gone half the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.00,0:55:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And according to Xeno's paradox\Nthe rabbit never can catch up with the tortoise
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.00,0:55:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because at any point in time\Nhe's only half way
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.00,0:55:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,left.\NEven if it's only
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.00,0:55:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one millionth of an inch\Nhe still can't get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.00,0:55:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He still can't get there.\NNow I was telling you more
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.00,0:55:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about likelihoods.\NThe more often you choose
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.00,0:55:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the more likely you choose\Na certain choice
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.00,0:56:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with an infinite number of choices\Nthe more likely you are
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.00,0:56:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose that again.\NEach time you have an infinite possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.00,0:56:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you've\Nchosen this once
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.09,0:56:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially if you repeat the choice\Nquickly, quickly, quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.09,0:56:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of your choosing that again\Ngets higher and higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.09,0:56:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spiritual choice\Nto forgive, to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.09,0:56:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,gracious, etc.\NThe likelihood goes up
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.09,0:56:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will choose that again.\NSo this also reflects intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.09,0:56:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And we spoke of the work\Nof the doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.13,0:56:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,whose name begins with an M\NI forget now.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.19,0:56:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The work on intention.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.44,0:56:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That intention\Nthen says
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.44,0:56:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so your intention.\NYou're stating your intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.44,0:56:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That intention now greatly increases\Nthe likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.44,0:57:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of certain choices.\NSo this is partly an argument to free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.44,0:57:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is the argument\Nthat there is no such thing as free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.44,0:57:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But it ignores\Nwhat we just got through saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.44,0:57:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There is dominance of choice.\NSo when you make a dominant choice in this direction
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.44,0:57:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then you influence\Nthe whole field.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.44,0:57:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The likelihood\Nis much greater that you will choose
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.44,0:57:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a positive option the next time also.\NSo the holier
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.67,0:57:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you get, the holier you get.\NAnd the worser you get, the worser
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.03,0:57:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you get.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.13,0:57:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,people who are into spiritual integrity\Nwill, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.13,0:57:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,admit a mistake as soon as\Nthey make it and say, I just made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.13,0:57:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you\Ndon't want its energy to be out there
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.42,0:57:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and attract other mistakes.\NSo if you call it by its name
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.42,0:57:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,say, you know, that was a mistake\Nyou made a name wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.42,0:57:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody from history\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.42,0:58:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,80 year memory is not as great as it was at 30\Nyou know, you can forget a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.42,0:58:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when there is so much\Npublicity about them, their name gets bandied
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.42,0:58:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about so much that you begin to confuse it\Nwith other people in the same
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.42,0:58:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,time era.\NSo the important thing was to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.48,0:58:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that a double personality can exist.\NThey do exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.61,0:58:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Their effect on our life\Nhas been devastating.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.65,0:58:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a true clinical condition\Nand it is a strange
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.65,0:58:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. I've never researched\Nthe karma of why there's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.65,0:58:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,two different personalities in one\Nbody. And they trade off
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.65,0:58:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,time with each other. They trade off\Nyou've had them for two weeks now
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.84,0:58:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for God's sake.\NI haven't even been able to kill anybody for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.13,0:58:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And that guy comes on\Nokay, let's go and have a good time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.36,0:58:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and stab some people to death.\NStab some children and a nice widow or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.36,0:58:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pow, pow, pow.\NBang. That one goes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.61,0:58:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now this one has to go to jail because of this one.\NAnd of course there's famous criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.61,0:59:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Famous serial criminals\Nthat are alternate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.73,0:59:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,personalities. You remember the one\Nthat killed Sam
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.86,0:59:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or something like that. God was speaking to him\Nto kill people.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.17,0:59:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question then\Nis a judicial one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.17,0:59:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to imprison the innocent one\Nbecause the criminal
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.17,0:59:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,one\Nis a criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.55,0:59:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were going to ask me a question, huh?\NYes. At consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.55,0:59:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,levels below enlightenment\Nis there a personal me or does it just
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.11,0:59:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, are you asking about the reality of it\Nor the illusion of it? There
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.11,0:59:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200\NYeah, there is a
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.78,0:59:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,personal me. Yeah, there's a\Nme. It assumes that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.36,0:59:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the experiencer\Nprimarily. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.36,0:59:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as you get higher you become more aware\Nthat you're the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.36,1:00:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,field which\Nis able to identify that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.36,1:00:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the below\N200 people exist but they don't
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.36,1:00:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,really comprehend the\Nsignificance of existence. People say
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.55,1:00:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,how can that be? Well\Nif you comprehended the value of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.90,1:00:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be able to kill anybody.\NIt's only when they no longer are
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.90,1:00:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,real to you that you can kill them.\NSo below
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.28,1:00:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,200 people are dangerous because\Nthey do not value your
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.28,1:00:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,life. They do not\Nvalue your life. They can blow up a whole
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.67,1:00:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,busload of children.\NAnd they don't feel bad about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.71,1:00:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They themselves don't experience the\Nvalue of their own
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.71,1:00:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,life as a divine gift. Therefore\Nthey don't value it in others.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.71,1:00:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you don't value your own money\Nyou don't value other people's money either.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.76,1:00:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nit sounds strange to say that people below
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.71,1:00:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,200 are not aware that they\Nexist. But I'm telling you about the word
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.71,1:01:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness. They exist but they're not really\Naware that they exist as such.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.71,1:01:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And above 200 but\Nstill below enlightenment, is there a personal
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.88,1:01:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,me? Oh there very definitely is a\Npersonal operation of a personal me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.38,1:01:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation is very much\Na very personal me. And we spend all
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.48,1:01:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,our time worrying about it actually.\NThe personal me
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.48,1:01:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,until you begin to transcend it\Nand see that it's autonomous.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.48,1:01:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to see the things that are happening\Nautonomously. However
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.48,1:01:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the autonomous choices\Nare a consequence of that with
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.48,1:01:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which you have aligned. So\Nas you choose a higher and higher
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.48,1:01:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment even though\Nthey're spontaneous as Medina's
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.48,1:01:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,research shows\Nthe choices now begin
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.48,1:01:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to show a preference for that\Nwhich is benign and harmless and aligned
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.48,1:01:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with truth rather than\Nthe other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.80,1:01:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention set. So Medina calls\Nit attention set.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.92,1:02:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention set.\NSo you have
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.51,1:02:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,intention and attention\Nset.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.51,1:02:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And these tend to dominate it.\NThese are dominant fields
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.57,1:02:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.\NSo you might picture fields
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.57,1:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of progressive power.\NAnd the smaller little
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.59,1:02:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,fields like the weather down here\Nis being dominated by
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.59,1:02:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a more powerful weather field\Nwhich is dominated by an even higher
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.59,1:02:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,weather field. So\Nby commitment then
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.01,1:02:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing is you're setting\Nthe predominant overall field
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.01,1:02:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of which\Nlesser and lesser choices are being made.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.01,1:02:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's still\Nfreedom of the will but it is only
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.30,1:02:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,within certain fields.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.30,1:02:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness really has\Nto do with energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.30,1:02:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy fields of increasing\Npower and dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.65,1:02:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So your spiritual self eventually\Nbecomes the most powerful aspect
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.65,1:03:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as you go over 200.\NThe etheric
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.71,1:03:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,body forms, the etheric brain forms,\Nyou develop
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.71,1:03:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a personal karma\Nand kundalini
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.71,1:03:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,energy dominates\Nhow your brain functions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.71,1:03:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brain begins\Nreleasing endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.84,1:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These endorphins\Ninstead of adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.00,1:03:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the endorphins give you\Na right brain
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.00,1:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brain\Ndominated by endorphins sees
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.00,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,life as pretty much benign.\NSees life as relatively
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.00,1:03:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,benign.\NWith the proviso as I said
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.19,1:03:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of not being the fool.\NSimultaneously not playing the fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.76,1:03:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh aren't they nice?\NWho just said that just left the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.76,1:03:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't they nice? It's just a nice doggy.\NNo that is a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.76,1:04:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And he will eat you up.\NNot because he hates you but because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.76,1:04:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he's hungry. Oh I see.\NTigers are not evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.76,1:04:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They just want you for dinner.\NShould be a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.38,1:04:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He says\NI want you for dinner baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.98,1:04:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So that gets you off good and evil\Nwhen you see that each thing is only being
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.98,1:04:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's able to be\Nat any point in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.11,1:04:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If it could be different than it is\Nit would be. Therefore we can't
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.11,1:04:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,condemn anybody or anything for being\Nwhat they are. So
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.11,1:04:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when I say beware of something\NI mean
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.11,1:04:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to beware of its upside and its downside.\NIt doesn't make it good
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.11,1:04:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or better or bad.\NIt's just that you see it for what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.11,1:04:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can't say\Na Komodo dragon is bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.11,1:04:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing bad about him.\NHe just likes to bite people.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.32,1:05:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it is to be a\NKomodo dragon. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.44,1:05:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Then at a certain level\Nof consciousness you don't have to come back
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.44,1:05:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as a Komodo dragon.\NThat's how you evolve from being a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.44,1:05:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Who's next?\NYes. I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.07,1:05:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes.\NI can't hear the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.96,1:05:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dominant. Yes.\NIt becomes progressively
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.76,1:05:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,dominant as you\Nbecome aligned with the desire to reach
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.76,1:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth. The capacity\Nto discern perception from
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.76,1:06:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,essence does not really\Nmanifest until about
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.80,1:06:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 300.\NWhich is the opening
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.80,1:06:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the third eye of the Buddhic body.\NThe third eye of the etheric Buddhic body.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.80,1:06:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the higher bodies.\NAnd when the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.00,1:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,opening of the third eye\Nis called discernment.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.00,1:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So discernment is not really\Ndominant
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.00,1:06:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until consciousness level\N600.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.67,1:06:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to that time\None can be deceived quite easily.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.98,1:06:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600\Nyou sense
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.98,1:06:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the wolf in the sheep's clothing.\NAnd like with
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.80,1:06:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration I sense something out.\NAnd then I calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.88,1:06:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it and I say yes I got\Nwhat the second personality is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.88,1:06:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you begin\Nto sense it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.88,1:06:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's at\N600. 600 is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.03,1:07:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the first level of true\Nenlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.03,1:07:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,570 is saintliness.\N580, 590 is joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.03,1:07:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstasy.\NAnd finally at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.32,1:07:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an incredible\Ncalm. There is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.67,1:07:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially the\Npeace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.90,1:07:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And one doesn't really have to remain here\Nany further.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.90,1:07:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600 you have permission to leave.\NAnd it's a state of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.28,1:07:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite peace.\NAnd infinite oneness beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.69,1:07:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,all description.\NThe peace of God beyond all understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.82,1:07:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is what you hear in\Nchurch and sermons. The peace of God
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.82,1:07:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all understanding.\NIt emerges at level 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.82,1:07:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say at that level\Nyou can leave. And 50%
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.23,1:07:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of people who reach that level do leave.\NYou're invited to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.53,1:07:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say it's almost invitational\Nto
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.78,1:07:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,do so. And then for reasons\Nremembered
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.82,1:08:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or not\Nremembered
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.82,1:08:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the choice is made.\NBut again one is sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.82,1:08:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness to the choice. So when it\Nhappens one doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.82,1:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,know whether they're going to walk on or not\Nwalk on. And it's not really
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.30,1:08:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your problem. There isn't any of you\Nleft to worry about it. So no choice
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.30,1:08:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be made. It seems\Nto be a karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.61,1:08:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And my own condition\NI sort of intuited
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.61,1:08:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with an agreement.\NWith the fulfillment of an
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.61,1:08:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,agreement prior\Nto this incarnation. And I witnessed
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.61,1:08:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the agreement\Ntaking place. You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.61,1:08:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an agreement\Nthat you agreed to fulfill.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.61,1:08:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people\Nmay not be aware that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.02,1:08:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,such a thing goes on in their life. But I think\Nall of us have made agreements
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.09,1:08:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and promises and that these\Nare playing a part in our life
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.09,1:09:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,right now. Everybody\Nhere has obviously made a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.09,1:09:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual agreement, commitment or declaration\Nor they wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.09,1:09:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is not a class on bull fighting.\NHow to gore a bull.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.09,1:09:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously\Neveryone here has made one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.09,1:09:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Some don't consciously\Nremember it in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.09,1:09:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But to be attracted to such a group\Nand a group that calibrates as high as this
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.09,1:09:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to have made such a commitment.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.18,1:09:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.52,1:09:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't identify a witness observer.\NWell yes you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.52,1:09:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,At first you realize that\Nthere's
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.71,1:09:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the witnessing and the observing.\NAnd you observe them as phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.71,1:09:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,not as a personage.\NThere's no watcher and no witness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.71,1:09:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as an entity.\NThere's only these functions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.71,1:10:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that witnessing and watching\Nare going on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.71,1:10:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And these go on\Nindependently of your
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.73,1:10:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have any say so\Nabout it. In other words it's an aspect
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.73,1:10:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.\NUnless you were witnessing and watching
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.09,1:10:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't know how to respond to the world.\NSo the witnessing and the watching
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.09,1:10:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are automatic phenomena.\NAnd therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.09,1:10:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the farther you get back\Nto the observer and then the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.09,1:10:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and then finally\Nwhat is it that's witnessing and observing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.09,1:10:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,brings you back to conscious awareness.\NYou realize
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.09,1:10:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that what's going on is awareness\Nof these phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.09,1:10:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's closer to your reality\Nis the awareness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.09,1:10:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That your inner reality\Nis the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.15,1:10:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of consciousness.\NNo, because there's still
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.76,1:11:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,an illusion beyond that.\NThe illusion has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.94,1:11:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see\Nthat there is someone
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.68,1:11:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that has\Nit has to do with the life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.68,1:11:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that one identifies\Nthese phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.89,1:11:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as life.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.11,1:11:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the last story I can remember\Nhad to do with relinquishing
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.81,1:11:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire\Nto be.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.85,1:11:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to be\Nwas somehow associated with life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.98,1:11:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That if one gave up\Nlife one would no longer be.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.39,1:11:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the block was\Nto surrender the source
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.65,1:11:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of life itself to divinity.\NThe only thing left
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.85,1:11:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,was the\Nthought that I exist
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.28,1:12:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I exist because of\Nlife. And the source of life
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.77,1:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so just as I had\Nlaid down ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.18,1:12:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,joy\Nand each thing as it arose
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.18,1:12:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing left\Nwith which I
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.27,1:12:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,identified except life itself.\NAnd therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.47,1:12:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a knowingness\Nthis too oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.92,1:12:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,do I surrender to thee.\NAnd I surrendered life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.94,1:12:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Nwent through actual experience
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.94,1:12:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of death and it was agony.\NIt was agony but the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.14,1:12:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,agony was only\Nfor moments.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.59,1:12:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One actually feels one's self\Nwith a small s
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.59,1:12:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,actually die.\NIt actually dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.88,1:12:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And you experience the death agony.\NAnd beyond that the door opens
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.31,1:12:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and excels his deal.\NGlory to God shines forth
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.78,1:13:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is all the radiance of all existence.\NThen you're beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.30,1:13:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all of that.\NWhat did we do at 3 o'clock?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.44,1:13:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh\NI thought I had some spiritual duty to perform
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.06,1:13:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a quick break.\NTake a quick break.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.18,1:13:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a quick break.\NGod bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.01,1:13:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to say thank you for everything.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.01,1:13:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we should say hi from Cornelia from Germany.\NOh yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.01,1:13:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She's doing the Cologne seminar.\NShe's very excited.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.80,1:13:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very nice. Thank you.\NAnd maybe you can talk about
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.89,1:13:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending the attachment to personal love.\NAttachment to personal love.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.68,1:14:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's a statuation
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.75,1:14:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,run by your endocrine system hormone.\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.84,1:14:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a craving.\NCravingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.53,1:14:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Cravingness is coming out of your animal.\NTry to replace the cravingness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.10,1:14:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lovingness.\NBecause cravingness is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.10,1:14:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm deficient and I need to get.\NLovingness is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.23,1:14:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you complete my\Nfulfill my
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.93,1:14:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness.\NSo one is I have to have
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.86,1:14:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coming from one's\Nanimal instinctual nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.86,1:14:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippopotamuses do it.\NElephants do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.69,1:14:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got to do it.\NBeing a young male is not an enviable
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.76,1:15:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,place in life frankly.\NTo transcend it requires
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.57,1:15:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you how to\Ntranscend it. How to transcend any
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.00,1:15:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,desire of a physical nature\NHow to overcome a craving.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.35,1:15:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A craving\Nfirst starts in your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.38,1:15:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as an image.\NIf you watch this carefully
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.07,1:15:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see any craving\Nfirst appears as an image.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.07,1:15:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's a cheeseburger or a hamburger\Nthe naked body of the opposite sex
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.18,1:15:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or if you're an alcoholic a drinker.\NFirst comes the image of the drink
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.52,1:15:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't eliminate it instantly\Nit draws energy to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.52,1:15:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So when it first appears\Nit's only about five watts.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.63,1:15:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you eliminate it within the first second\Nit's 150 watts and it's 600 watts
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.63,1:15:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's a have to.\NYou can interrupt
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.47,1:15:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the progression by interrupting\Nthe image.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.85,1:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you look at something\Na cheeseburger or whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.64,1:16:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't just the cheeseburger\Nit's instantly now you have an image of the cheeseburger
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.64,1:16:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in your mind and that's what you crave.\NTherefore you have to be very fast
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.68,1:16:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and see\Nthe object of the cravingness
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.19,1:16:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,appear in your consciousness\Nand make a choice to eliminate it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.19,1:16:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NThat's how you do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.21,1:16:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was telling alcoholics\Nyou've got about one or two seconds
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.21,1:16:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to eliminate that image of a drink.\NIn the book Alcoholics Anonymous
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.68,1:16:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it talks about some guy who was sober\N14 years or something, 11 years
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.68,1:16:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he walked across\Nin the hall or something of a hotel
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.94,1:16:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the image of a martini\Ncame into his mind
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.94,1:16:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and mindlessly he walked to the bar\Nand after 13, 14 years
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.94,1:16:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of sobriety\Nrelapsed and got drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.30,1:17:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was in that one second.\NSo you'll see that in the AA book
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.30,1:17:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in which\Nthe early members recount their experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.73,1:17:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that out of nowhere\Nsuddenly appeared
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.67,1:17:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the image of the martini.\NThat's when he had his chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.67,1:17:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When he didn't eliminate the martini\Nthat instant he automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.67,1:17:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,walked over to the bar\Nand lost 14 years of sobriety.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.56,1:17:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't like consciously choose\Nhe just didn't have the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.90,1:17:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness technique\Nthe spiritual technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.15,1:17:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? That's a secret.\NDon't tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.51,1:17:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A short question on the technique of surrender\Nas you described it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.51,1:17:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,like in the final run\Nand like maybe more like
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.51,1:17:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a confirmation maybe\Nwhen the sword is there
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.51,1:18:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,every sword has a hook\Nor a choose
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.64,1:18:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and what I'm doing is\Ntry to intuit the choose
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.64,1:18:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so then the thought process\Nfalls away?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.64,1:18:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you're trying to\Neliminate thought before it reaches
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.76,1:18:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the formation of the thought.\NEventually, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.02,1:18:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel the image\Nof a dogginess coming up
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.02,1:18:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the nothingness\Narises a dogginess
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.02,1:18:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,big dogginess and then it becomes\Na dog, then it becomes an old rover
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.02,1:18:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,then it becomes how an old rover got hit by the car\Nand then how we all cried
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.02,1:18:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was my daughter's third birthday\Nand the whole family was sad
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.23,1:18:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's a whole long tale\Nso you have to catch it as it emerges.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.50,1:18:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way\Nto give up the choose
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.50,1:18:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the best way to do it?\NTo give up wanting to have it?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.52,1:18:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the image\NI can't really tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.27,1:19:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,how to do that. You have to\Nexperiment with it and reflect on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.27,1:19:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't\Nallow, you feel the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.76,1:19:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness begin to arise\Nand now it's going to spill forth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.76,1:19:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,figure.\NSo you let go the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.85,1:19:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of wanting to think\Nearlier and earlier
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.85,1:19:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the process.\NIt feels like a desire?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.85,1:19:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes it is, that's correct.\NA desire to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.60,1:19:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to feel like an attack\Nof thinkingness is coming on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.60,1:19:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's that much thinking\Ndon't meditate, do something else
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.38,1:19:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until it's gone.\NThat's very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.67,1:19:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of no form\Nit begins to gather form
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.67,1:19:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and as it gathers form it gathers energy.\NAnd by the time it gets to over over
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.72,1:20:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you've got to run over by the truck\Nit's too late already.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.48,1:20:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay on the advancing edge\Njust prior to thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.07,1:20:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see your thinkingness\Nas just amusement anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.22,1:20:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins,\Nrecently I've been shown to be aware
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.22,1:20:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of my\Nself-centeredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.22,1:20:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.\NGet closer to the mic and speak slowly.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.22,1:20:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently I've been made to be aware\Nof self-centeredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.22,1:20:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My self-centeredness?\NSelf-centeredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.22,1:20:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.\NAnd I want to ask you how to work on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.28,1:20:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it's like self-centeredness\Nis watching yourself in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.57,1:20:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So give up watching yourself in the movie.\NSee they're signing the book, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.60,1:21:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I could also be\Naware of who's signing the book
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.77,1:21:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fact that you're signing a book.\NLook at all that, it's boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.43,1:21:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's boring.\NThat's how self-centeredness can be.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.18,1:21:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm sitting in the chair\Nand I'm talking to Dr. Hawkins
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.18,1:21:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see how boring all that is?\NSo that's a self,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.43,1:21:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know,\Nsort of like you're doing a video
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.92,1:21:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of yourself at the same time.\NYou see what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.11,1:21:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a habit of thought.\NIt's a habit of thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.11,1:21:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you're aware that you're doing it\Nas a habit, it tends to diminish.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.78,1:21:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do what you're doing\Nwithout being aware that there's a you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.23,1:21:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,see?\NThat happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.18,1:22:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't say, well Dr. Hawkins,\NI think while I'm talking to her
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.18,1:22:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wave my hands in the air\Nand go blah blah blah blah blah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.18,1:22:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how boring that would be?\NIt would kill the spontaneity of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.31,1:22:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Intuitively you try to respond\Nin a nonverbal manner because
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.31,1:22:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise people mentalize\Na mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.76,1:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Spontaneously just be that which you are\Nwithout any comment, without any witnessing of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.39,1:22:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They say when you scramble eggs\Ndon't be saying, gee how good am I
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.68,1:22:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,scrambling these eggs.\NThat ruins the eggs for one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.90,1:22:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like one's higher self\Nknows all these things
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.92,1:22:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have to track it\Nwith your lower self.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.30,1:22:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just noticing it tends to diminish it.\NJust noticing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.30,1:22:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NI don't say, now I am sitting in a chair
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.77,1:23:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on a pillow and talking to you.\NI don't say that, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.13,1:23:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sort of saying, now I'm sitting in a chair\Ntalking to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.13,1:23:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I want you to do is get bored with\Nself observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.06,1:23:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mindfulness is something else.\NWe're talking about now self observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.06,1:23:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mindfulness will tell you that\Nyou're hooked in self observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.06,1:23:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you're complaining about.\NBut that came out of mindfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.06,1:23:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something better.\NMindfulness is okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.82,1:23:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have mindfulness\Nthat's why you're complaining about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.77,1:23:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you weren't mindful you wouldn't know\Nand you just think that's the way I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.92,1:24:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means good progress.\NWhere do these come from?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.65,1:24:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. Hello.\NI've simplified this question as much as I can
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.94,1:24:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins.\NI don't seem to have enough physical energy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.94,1:24:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to do what I want to do right now.\NAnd I want to know
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.23,1:24:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what the obstacle is blocking\Nmy physical energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.68,1:24:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention may not be as strong as you\NI mean
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.68,1:24:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're into ought to, ought to\Nthis and ought to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.89,1:24:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the hypothetical.\NHow do you know the ought to has any
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.89,1:24:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,reality to it?\NI ought to be peeling more potatoes than I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.17,1:24:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I ought to be able to peel eight\Nand I only peel four.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.72,1:24:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's projecting the hypothetical.\NWhy not just settle for the real?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.72,1:24:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only peel four potatoes at this time\Nin your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.77,1:25:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't invite a lot of company for dinner.\NCan I do a follow up?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.81,1:25:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean\NI think along the spiritual pathway there's
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.81,1:25:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,periods, sometimes long periods\Nwhere your capacity to function is really curtailed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.88,1:25:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Really curtailed.\NYou say
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.21,1:25:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I have the energy to\Nput my shoes and socks
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.56,1:25:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,on today.\NSomehow the instinct of survival
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.90,1:25:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,takes over and you do what you need\Nto do.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.11,1:25:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wouldn't worry about it.\NBetween expectation and
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.11,1:25:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,actual capacity.\NIn spiritual endeavor a great deal of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.69,1:25:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,goes into the spiritual work\Nand you don't realize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.11,1:25:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But\Nit siphons off a lot of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.36,1:25:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that would otherwise go into physicality\Nand movement, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.07,1:26:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThere are periods where you do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.75,1:26:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent several years just meditating\Nand doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.18,1:26:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the view of the world, doing nothing.\NSat cross-legged for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.52,1:26:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NBlack widow spiders were underneath the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.52,1:26:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,seat in fact.\NOne time I looked down there and
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.57,1:26:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just sitting there meditating\Nin this place for years
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.57,1:26:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and there were black widow spiders\Nliving under the chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.23,1:26:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Evil spirits, huh?\NYeah.
